Important:
1. Import speedup for gene annotation initialization on MySQL Databases
2. Export TSV tables for pheno, feature, expression, DGE tables
  roger get-expression-matrix GEO1234 --outfile /my/out/file
  roger get-dge-result used_contrast used_design GEO1234
  roger show-pheno-matrix    # prints (except) to display
3. Convenience methods for defining / importing design & contrast matrices:
  roger add-design --use-pheno-column "SAMPLE_GROUP" --group-levels # or --group-levels-file
  roger add-contrast --make-contrasts='["CmpDX": "Threat23", "Bla": "Blub"]'
4. Add update utility for matrix data, e.g.:
  roger update-pheno         # Reload pheno data from PhenoSrc field
  roger update-pheno --file /new/pheno/data.tsv
5. Quality checking for gene annotation import:
   When importing genes, try to filter out potential "junk genes", e.g. Don't include ensembl identifiers that point to unmapped chromosome region
6 Choosing web front end stack
  * d3.js + Flask,
  * plotly + Flask + Dash, <- My preference for now, since good compromise between quality & development time. But not a full-blown conclusion yet
  * PlainR + shiny
7 Visualization of gene distributions
  Plain Web site where one select study and then the gene to visualize etc
8 Visualization of DGE results
  Select Study -> visualize dge + render plots

Backlog:
* Add GSE analysis for limam and edgeR
* Add DEseq2 as DGE algorithm
* Adding cli-commands for generating reports / plots
* Provide REST interface alongside to the CLI commands
* Move DGE table processing code from ribiosROGER into this package, make ribiosROGER a pure client-API (e.g. provides wrappers for the REST calls)
* Add support for microarray CEL files (for now, only normalized data is supported)
* Better format for object identification, e.g.: StudyName:DesigName:ContrastName
  roger add-contrast my/file.tsv StudyName:MyDesign   # creates new contrast for design MyDesign in StudyName
  roger add-contrast my/file.tsv StudyName:MyDesign:MyNewContrast # also add name for the contrast file
  roger add-contrast my/file.tsv StudyName::NewContrast # make design specification optional if there is only one design matrix
* MongoDB interaction: Pass reference to a MongoDB installation,
* Add DEseq DGE analysis
* Add dynamic mechanism to extend ROGEr by other modules:
  roger add-dge-method-ma betterLimma /path/to/betterLimma.R # will execute betterLimma.R with all required data exported to a temp file
  roger add-ges-method hdCAMERA /path/to/hdCAMERA.R
* Auxilary:
  * Add ability to specify explicit version or gene annotation datasets (e.g. use Ensembl 92)
  * Add more sophisticated query function for local BioMart annotation queries
  * Add more information to feature annotation when generating model objects (i.e. add GeneSymbol, EntrezGeneID and Gene description)